HEADWORD: Jackstay
<hw>Jack"stay`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A rail of wood or iron stretching along a yard of a vessel, to
which the sails are fastened.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

